<title>UK: Kenneth Clarke joins F&amp;C trust as director.</title>
<headline>Kenneth Clarke joins F&amp;C trust as director.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Foreign &amp; Colonial Investment Trust said on Thursday that former Chancellor of the Exchequer Kenneth Clarke had joined as a non-executive director</p>
<p>&quot;He's obviously got terrific knowledge and experience of economics and finance,&quot; fund manager Jeremy Tigue told Reuters. &quot;We think he is going to be very valuable to us.&quot;</p>
<p>Clarke will be paid 18,000 sterling a year, Tigue said.</p>
<p>Also appointed non-executive director is British Steel finance director John Rennocks.</p>
<p>-- James Saft, London newsroom +171 542 2734</p>
